HEADWORD: Foison
<hw>Foi"son</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>foison</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>fusio</ets> a pouring, effusion. See <er>Fusion</er>.]</ety>
<def>Rich harvest; plenty; abundance.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Lowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> That from the seedness the bare fallow brings⟦br⟧
To teeming <qex>foison</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

